*   ## **_Trick or Treat Tornado Tag: Darby Allin and Orange Cassidy def Daniel Garcia and Wheeler Yuta_**
    

Fun little No DQ brawl that ends when Orange Cassidy takes out Daniel Garcia with a tope through a table allowing Darby to tap Yuta out in the Scorpion Deathlock

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/948616ba-6933-4e53-be3e-502f521a2d53/21842.jpg?format=original)

Hook says he's aiming to take out his former partner Samoa Joe because he's shown the world who he truly is now.. Joe is the person Hook always knew he was

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/417c9701-875f-4c6c-8fd8-dc641902cead/21855.jpg?format=original)

The Young Bucks having flashbacks when they see a StayPuft Marshmallow dude backstage at Dynamite this week

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/67486979-180b-4a09-8124-878b26b9428c/21854.jpg?format=original)

Don Callis is trying to recruit the Young Bucks to the Don Callis Family so he gets their entrance music and pyro back (Which scares the shit out of them)

Callis even does a personal introduction for the Bucks 💀

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/e789cda0-bb6b-4609-a6da-8f817afabf3e/processed_21860.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_AEW World Tag Team Championship Number One Contenders: FTR def JetSPEED, the Young Bucks and Jurassic Express_**
    

FTR will face Brodido for the AEW World Tag Team Championships at Full Gear

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/86b1f988-c351-4dc2-a961-9bd45ed182ee/21863.jpg?format=original)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1a218485-f628-48d3-8b0a-4cf66dd13e3d/21870.jpg?format=original)

Don Callis is having a Don Callis Family summit to keep the peace in the family.

Callis claimed Takeshita could not be here because of travel issues.

Rocky Romero reveals a new DCF painting of the entire family. Josh Alexander shows off a video package highlighting DCF dominance. Kyle Fletcher is reading a promise he wrote when Takeshita shows up!!

Okada and Takeshita are about to get into it when Don Callis interrupted. He says Takeshita was the first Alpha but this is a family of Alphas now. They all need to listen to Don Callis.

Callis tells Takeshita to shake Okada's hand. Takeshita won't do it. Callis yells at Takeshita to shake his hand damnit. Takeshita won't do it.

Finally Callis tells Takeshita to do it for him. Takeshita actually tries and Okada flips him off.

Don Callis forces both men to team up on Collision this Saturday to show the world that the DCF does in fact get along

